title: Prime London Property Isn’t Looking So Hot
text:
Prime London Property Isn’t Looking So Hot October 10, 2015 
As an investment, swanky London homes are having a tough year. And it looks like next year won’t be much better. 
Property broker Knight Frank has cut its 2016 forecast for prime central London homes to 2% growth from 4.5%. The revision comes after annual price growth fell to 1.3% in September from 5% at the end of last year.
